li.p:
the matrix \adjoint{A} that satisfies
 \inprod{\uvec{u}}{A \uvec{v}} = \inprod{\adjoint{A} \uvec{u}}{\uvec{v}} 
for every pair of column vectors \uvec{u},\uvec{v} in V

a matrix for which \adjoint{A} = A,
so that A satisfies
 \inprod{\uvec{u}}{A \uvec{v}} = \inprod{A \uvec{u}}{\uvec{v}} 
for every pair of column vectors \uvec{u},\uvec{v} in V;
usually called symmetric in the real context and Hermitian in the complex context

a real matrix A that satisfies
 {\inprod{A \uvec{u}}{A \uvec{v}}}_{\R} = {\inprod{\uvec{u}}{\uvec{v}}}_{\R} 
for every pair of column vectors \uvec{u},\uvec{v} in \R^n

a complex matrix A that satisfies
 {\inprod{A \uvec{u}}{A \uvec{v}}}_{\C} = {\inprod{\uvec{u}}{\uvec{v}}}_{\C} 
for every pair of column vectors \uvec{u},\uvec{v} in \C^n

a matrix A that satisfies
 \inprod{A \uvec{u}}{A \uvec{v}} = \inprod{\uvec{u}}{\uvec{v}} 
for every pair of column vectors \uvec{u},\uvec{v} in V
